sec.p:
The genus Panophrys was established by Rao & Yang (1997) , based on the differences on its karyotype, morphology, and ecology. Different generic suggestions were proposed according to subsequent morphological systematic studies, regarding Panophrys as a subgenus or synonymy of Xenophrys or Megophrys (
Delorme et al. 2006
; Li & Wang 2008 ;
Fei et al. 2009
). However, recent comprehensive phylogenetic analyses have unanimously substantiated that Panophrys represents a monophyletic group, separated from Xenophrys , Megophrys , and all other clades within the subfamily (
Chen et al. 2017
;
Mahony et al. 2017
;
Liu et al. 2018
).

As for the recognition on the genus level on Panophrys and other monophyletic groups within the subfamily Megophryinae , the major point is the morphological differentiation among these groups, especially the differences between Panophrys and Xenophrys (
Chen et al. 2017
;
Mahony et al. 2017
;
Li et al. 2020
). The identification of Asian horned toad species based solely on traditional morphological characters has been somewhat ambiguous (
Li et al. 2014
;
Mahony et al. 2017
;
Liu et al. 2018
), which led previously to underestimated diversity and the controversial systematics. However, anurans are characterized by generally conservative, plesiomophic phenotypes (
Cherty et al. 1978
), and many other higher frog taxa have also been the subject of similar debates (e.g., Frost 2006 ; Li et al. 2008;
Duellman et al. 2016
;
Lyu et al. 2017
;
Arifin et al. 2018
). Furthermore, despite extensive stasis in evolution of morphological features, other aspects of these organisms (e.g., the genotype) continue differentiating (
Wilson et al. 1977
; Schopf 1984 ;
Avise et al. 1994
). Hence the separate evolutionary histories of the different groups should be studied in detail. The different clades of Asian horned toads have been revealed to undergo different histories due to the raise of Himalayas from Paleocene to Oligocene, which accelerates their rapid divergences and forms their current geographical distribution patterns (
Liu et al. 2018
). Additionally, it is very common that a taxon might be diagnosable from its sister group by specific characters, while the same character occurs in a third but distant taxon (
Vences et al. 2013
). Despite the morphological similarity between Panophrys and Xenophrys , Panophrys can be distinctly distinguished from its sister Ophryophryne which is regarded as an independent genus for long time ( Boulenger 1903 ; Dubois 1987 ;
Delorme et al. 2006
; Fei & Ye 2016 ). Finally, the Asian horned toads currently contain over 100 recognized species. In consideration of the additional large numbers of undescribed cryptic species and dramatically underestimated diversity within the Asian horned toads (
Chen et al. 2017
;
Mahony et al. 2017
;
Liu et al. 2018
;
Li et al. 2020
), it is inappropriate to place such many species within a single genus which is inconvenient for management ( Mayr 1942 ;
Vences et al. 2013
; comments on genus Lithobates Fitzinger, 1843 in Frost 2020 ).

